    <text id="A9807T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Patrick Brady writes to A. H. H. Stuart regarding a lawsuit settlement and a
                    missing ledger.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Alex H H Stuart Esq</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-06-24">June 24/67</date>
                        <name type="place">Philad<hi rend="super">a</hi></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have Yours of the 21. to hand this morning. I wrote you the same day in
                    reference to <add hand="h1" place="inline">the</add> abduction of my Ledger, to
                    which I refer you.</p>
                <p>It is difficult for me to say what Sum I would be willing to accept in Settlement
                    of my claim against Brady, taking all the Circumstances in the Case into account
                    I beg you will try and get the best offer possible when I will advise You at
                    once whether I will accept it or not.</p>
                <p><pb n="2"/>I have no desire to expose him in Case I can get a great settlement
                    from him.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully Yours,</salute>
                    <signed>P Brady</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
